%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Terrorist%20Acts%20in%20the%20UAPA%20and%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%3A%20Duplication%20or%20Duplicity%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F08%2F20135913%2Fscales-of-justice-flickr.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CConsistency%20is%20the%20hallmark%20of%20the%20unimaginative.%E2%80%9D%20(Oscar%20Wilde)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20greatest%20respect%20to%20Wilde%2C%20if%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%20were%20to%20embark%20upon%20a%20project%20as%20ambitious%20as%20%E2%80%9Cdecolonising%E2%80%9D%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%20%E2%80%93%20a%20law%20that%20has%20stood%20the%20test%20of%20time%20in%20many%20nations%20of%20the%20Commonwealth%2C%20such%20as%20Malaysia%2C%20Singapore%2C%20Pakistan%20and%20Mauritius%20%E2%80%93%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20%E2%80%9Cconsistency%E2%80%9D%20might%20not%20be%20that%20bad%20a%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELargely%20the%20work%20of%20Thomas%20Babington%20Macaulay%2C%20the%20IPC%20was%20the%20first%20codification%20of%20criminal%20law%20in%20the%20British%20Empire%20and%20is%20the%20longest-serving%20criminal%20code%20in%20the%20common%20law%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20informed%20by%20the%20ideas%20of%20utilitarian%20reformers%2C%20notably%20Jeremy%20Bentham%2C%20who%20advocated%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20reforms%20to%20English%20criminal%20law%20and%20its%20administration%20in%20the%20early%20nineteenth%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMacaulay%20embraced%20Bentham%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98science%20of%20legislation%E2%80%99%20and%20his%20aspiration%20for%20%E2%80%98universal%20jurisprudence%E2%80%99%20after%20he%20developed%20a%20close%20association%20with%20James%20Mill%20during%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20India%20Charter%20Act%2C%201833.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2011%2C%202023%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fgovt-withdraws-three-criminal-codes-to-replace-them-with-new-bills%2Farticle67628738.ece%5C%22%3EParliament%20of%20India%20was%20informed%20by%20Union%20home%20minister%3C%2Fa%3E%20Amit%20Shah%20that%20the%20IPC%3B%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%201973%20(CrPC)%20and%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%20(IEA)%20would%20be%20withdrawn%20and%20replaced%20by%20three%20new%20criminal%20codes%20after%20incorporating%20changes%20to%20them%20as%20recommended%20by%20a%20parliamentary%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20criminal%20codes%20which%20were%20sent%20to%20the%20parliamentary%20committee%20were%20widely%20criticised%20by%20the%20legal%20community%20as%20they%20were%20replete%20with%20mindless%20cut-and-paste%20and%20typographical%20bloopers!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2025%2C%20these%20Bills%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fthree-bills-to-replace-british-era-criminal-laws-get-presidents-assent%2Farticle67674266.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPresident%2520Draupadi%2520Murmu%2520on%2520December%2Ccleared%2520by%2520Parliament%2520last%2520week.%5C%22%3Ereceived%20presidential%20assent%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20reference%2C%20the%20three%20new%20criminal%20codes%20are%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(BNS)%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20(BNSS)%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Act%20(BSA)%2C%20which%20replace%20the%20IPC%2C%20CrPC%20and%20IEA%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F02%2FMacaulay_carousel.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-110276%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22429%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELargely%20the%20work%20of%20the%2019th-century%20historian%20and%20politician%20Thomas%20Macaulay%2C%20the%20IPC%20is%20the%20longest-serving%20criminal%20code%20in%20the%20common%20law%20world.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FPublic%20domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETerrorism%20makes%20its%20entry%20into%20a%20general%20penal%20law%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20113%20of%20the%C2%A0BNS%C2%A0seeks%20to%20bring%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%20act%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20new%20offence%2C%20as%20the%20IPC%20(its%20predecessor)%20did%20not%20have%20any%20provision%20to%20this%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20concern%20arises%20as%20the%20offences%20related%20to%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%20acts%E2%80%9D%20have%20already%20been%20defined%20in%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention%20Act)%20(UAPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20definition%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%20act%E2%80%9D%20under%20the%20BNS%20exactly%20mirrors%20the%20definition%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Dterrorist%20act%E2%80%9D%20under%20the%20UAPA.%20This%20makes%20the%20law%20vulnerable%20to%20being%20misused%2C%20as%20now%20a%20superintendent%20of%20police%20shall%20have%20the%20discretion%20to%20book%20a%20person%20either%20under%20the%20UAPA%20or%20the%20BNS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENo%20debate%20or%20discussion%2C%20hence%20second%20guessing%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Flok-sabha-passes-three-criminal-laws-that-replace-ipc-crpc-and-evidence-act-11703071827309.html%5C%22%3Esuspension%20of%20a%20total%20of%2097%20members%20of%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20three%20new%20criminal%20codes%20significantly%20curtailed%20the%20scope%20for%20any%20debate%2C%20discussion%20and%20deliberation%20on%20these%20legislative%20measures.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20there%20exists%20no%20parliamentary%20deliberation%20on%20the%20insertion%20of%20Section%20113%2C%20where%20the%20government%20could%20have%20been%20pressed%20to%20provide%20justifications%20for%20this%20potential%C2%A0duplication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20leaves%20us%20with%20only%20the%20option%20of%20%E2%80%9Csecond-guessing%E2%80%9D%20the%20impetus%20behind%20this%20legislative%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20it%20may%20suggest%20an%20attempt%20by%20the%20government%20to%20alter%20procedural%20aspects%20concerning%20investigating%20agencies%20in%20cases%20involving%20terrorist%20acts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20this%20were%20the%20case%2C%20a%20more%20judicious%20approach%20would%20involve%20addressing%20areas%20necessitating%20amendments%20or%20enhancements%20in%20the%20UAPA.%20Amending%20the%20existing%20law%20would%20obviate%20the%20need%20for%20unwarranted%20legislative%C2%A0duplication%2C%20preserving%20the%20integrity%20and%20effectiveness%20of%20the%20established%20legal%20framework%20provided%20by%20the%20UAPA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20111531%2FUntitled-design-5-1024x576.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20111531%2FUntitled-design-5-1024x576.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20111531%2FUntitled-design-5-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20111531%2FUntitled-design-5.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689963%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20suspension%20of%2097%20MPs%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20three%20new%20criminal%20codes%20significantly%20curtailed%20the%20scope%20for%20any%20debate%20on%20these%20legislative%20measures.%20Photo%3A%20Screenshot%20from%20X%2F%40KBanerjee_AITC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20possibility%20could%20be%20that%20the%20government%20might%20be%20acknowledging%20the%20potential%20for%20the%20misuse%20of%20the%20draconian%20UAPA%20and%20is%20thereby%20bringing%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%20acts%E2%80%9D%20into%20general%20law%20to%20allow%20them%20to%20be%20addressed%20through%20local%20state%20police%20procedures%20outlined%20in%20the%20BNSS%20(successor%20to%20the%20CrPC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20if%20this%20were%20the%20objective%2C%20one%20would%20expect%20a%20transparent%20discourse%20around%20and%20advertisement%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20intention%20to%20incorporate%20Section%20113%20into%20the%20BNS.%20The%20limited%20debate%20surrounding%20this%20matter%20raises%20vital%20questions%20regarding%20the%20clarity%20and%20communication%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20intent%20behind%20this%20legislative%20endeavour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EInsertion%20into%20the%20chapter%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98human%20body%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20penal%20law%20classifies%20offences%20into%20categories.%C2%A0Traditionally%2C%20offences%20related%20to%20terrorism%20were%20placed%20under%20a%20chapter%20dealing%20with%20%E2%80%9Coffences%20against%20the%20state%E2%80%9D.%20Curiously%2C%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%20act%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20new%20offence%20under%20the%20BNS%20is%20within%20the%20chapter%20dealing%20with%20%E2%80%9Coffences%20affecting%20the%20human%20body%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETerrorism%20often%20involves%20acts%20that%20extend%20beyond%20direct%20physical%20harm%20to%20individuals%20and%20encompass%20broader%20threats%20to%20national%20security%2C%20public%20order%20and%20societal%20stability.%C2%A0In%20fact%2C%20the%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cterrorism%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20BNS%20mechanically%20adopts%20the%20UAPA%20definition%2C%20which%20does%20not%20restrict%20the%20offence%20only%20to%20the%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20blowing%20up%20a%20strategic%20bridge%20with%20no%20bodily%20injury%20to%20any%20person%20would%20still%20qualify%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98terrorist%20act%E2%80%99.%C2%A0Could%20it%20be%20that%20by%20including%20the%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%20act%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20chapter%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Chuman%20body%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20government%20was%20and%20bringing%20only%20those%20acts%20directed%20at%20the%20human%20body%20within%20the%20general%20penal%20law%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20however%2C%20would%20be%20absurd%2C%20as%20terrorism%20by%20its%20very%20nature%20is%20focused%20on%20the%20consequences%20of%20the%20act%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20actual%20act%20itself%2C%20and%20such%20acts%20could%20be%20targeted%20at%20human%20lives%20or%20vital%20installations%20or%20even%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FnpHbecvfc9o%3Fsi%3DwoXJvZ5cYQHtVobt%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDuplication%20or%20duplicity%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20stated%2C%20it%20is%20unclear%20why%20the%20new%20offence%20of%20the%20terrorist%20act%20has%20been%20provided%20for%20in%20the%20BNS.%20What%20was%20the%20need%20for%20duplication%20when%20the%20UAPA%2C%20which%20is%20a%20special%20statute%2C%20already%20covers%20terrorist%20acts%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20striking%20similarity%20in%20the%20language%20of%20the%20definition%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98terrorist%20act%E2%80%99%20in%20both%20statutes%20raises%20grave%20doubts%20as%20to%20the%20intent%20behind%20such%20a%20move.%C2%A0In%20modern%20criminal%20law%20jurisprudence%2C%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20typically%20aims%20for%20precision%20and%20clarity%20in%20drafting%20legislation%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20confusion%20and%20ensure%20consistent%20interpretation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20presence%20of%20this%20duplicate%20definition%20in%20both%20the%20UAPA%20and%20BNS%20would%20lead%20to%20ambiguity%20in%20understanding%20its%20legislatively%20intended%20scope%20and%20application.%20Further%2C%20the%20rationale%20of%20this%20duplication%20becomes%20more%20susceptible%20to%20ambiguity%20as%20no%20explanation%20is%20provided%20by%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsansad.in%2FgetFile%2Frsnew%2FCommittee_site%2FCommittee_File%2FReportFile%2F15%2F188%2F246_2023_12_15.pdf%3Fsource%3Drajyasabha%5C%22%3Eparliamentary%20standing%20committee%20on%20home%20affairs%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20such%20a%20legislative%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20duplication%20of%20the%20definition%20under%20Section%20113%20of%20the%20newly%20enacted%20criminal%20code%20and%20the%20UAPA%20can%20be%20found%20in%20the%20comparative%20table%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02152903%2FPt7ty--726x1024.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22726%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02152903%2FPt7ty--726x1024.png%20726w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02152903%2FPt7ty--213x300.png%20213w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02152903%2FPt7ty-.png%20851w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695391%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20UAPA%20as%20a%20special%20statute%20and%20the%20rationale%20for%20a%20special%20law%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStatutes%20related%20to%20counterterrorism%20are%20often%20enacted%20to%20address%20threats%20to%20national%20security.%20These%20statutes%20grant%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20specific%20powers%20to%20deal%20with%20situations%20that%20may%20pose%20risks%20to%20the%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20a%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20types%20of%20offences%20are%20covered%20under%20special%20statutes%2C%20as%20they%20prescribe%20heightened%20penalties%20for%20offenses%20falling%20within%20their%20purview.%20This%20may%20serve%20as%20a%20deterrent%20and%20convey%20the%20severity%20of%20certain%20actions%2C%20recognising%20the%20unique%20harm%20or%20threat%20posed%20by%20specific%20behaviours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20need%20for%20special%20statutes%20arises%20when%20the%20general%20laws%20of%20a%20country%20are%20not%20sufficient%20to%20address%20the%20unique%20needs%20or%20circumstances%20of%20a%20specific%20group%20or%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UAPA%20was%20enacted%20looking%20at%20the%20highly%20specialised%20and%20complex%20nature%20of%20terrorist%20activities%2C%20the%20need%20to%20deal%20with%20them%20through%20a%20different%20procedural%20law%20to%20address%20the%20intricacies%20involved%20and%20to%20provide%20detailed%20regulations%20that%20may%20not%20be%20adequately%20covered%20by%20general%20statutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDoctrine%20of%20harmonious%20construction%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20courts%20have%20consistently%20applied%20the%20%E2%80%9Crule%20of%20harmonious%20construction%E2%80%9D%20to%20resolve%20conflicts%20between%20the%20general%20and%20special%20provisions%20of%20%E2%80%98conflicting%E2%80%99%20laws.%20This%20legal%20maxim%20dictates%20that%20when%20there%20is%20an%20apparent%20conflict%20between%20two%20independent%20provisions%20of%20law%2C%20the%20provision%20of%20the%20special%20law%20must%20prevail%20over%20that%20of%20the%20general%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UAPA%20is%20the%20special%20law%20addressing%20terrorism%2C%20whereas%20the%20BNS%20is%20a%20general%20statute%20that%20addresses%20offences%20generally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20established%20precedent%20that%20in%20a%20situation%20involving%20both%20a%20general%20law%20and%20a%20special%20law%20addressing%20a%20specific%20aspect%20(in%20this%20case%20a%20terrorist%20act)%20that%20is%20covered%20by%20the%20general%20law%20(in%20this%20case%20the%20BNS)%2C%20the%20rule%20of%20harmonious%20construction%20is%20invoked%20and%20the%20special%20law%20prevails%20over%20the%20general.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20given%20that%20the%20UAPA%20will%20apply%20rather%20than%20Section%20113%20of%20the%20BNS%2C%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20insertion%20defies%20all%20logic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkhurram-parvez-uapa-india-kashmir-law%5C%22%3EThe%20UAPA%20Versus%20Khurram%20Parvez%2C%20an%20Extreme%20Law%20Versus%20a%20Rights%20Defender%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EImplications%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20us%20to%20understand%20the%20implications%20of%20this%20duplication%2C%20we%20will%20have%20to%20briefly%20understand%20how%20an%20investigation%20is%20proceeded%20under%20terrorist%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20discussed%2C%20the%20UAPA%20happens%20to%20be%20the%20special%20statute%20that%20deals%20with%20terrorist%20acts%2C%20which%20are%20mentioned%20as%20a%20scheduled%20offence%20under%20the%20National%20Investigation%20Act%2C%202008%2C%20thereby%20giving%20jurisdiction%20to%20the%20National%20Investigation%20Agency%20(NIA)%20to%20investigate%20such%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20process%20is%20that%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20receipt%20of%20the%20offence%2C%20the%20officer-in-charge%20of%20the%20police%20station%20is%20to%20forward%20a%20report%20to%20the%20state%20government%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20would%20forward%20it%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20as%20expeditiously%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20receiving%20the%20report%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20within%2015%20days%20determines%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20said%20report%20whether%20the%20offence%20is%20a%20scheduled%20offence%20(under%20the%20UAPA)%20and%20is%20fit%20to%20be%20investigated%20by%20the%20NIA%20by%20considering%20the%20%E2%80%9Dgravity%20of%20the%20offence%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Dother%20relevant%20factors.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20it%20is%20to%20be%20noted%20that%20if%20during%20the%20investigation%2C%20the%20NIA%20after%20due%20consideration%20of%20the%20certain%20factors%20thinks%20it%20would%20be%20beneficial%20or%20necessary%2C%20it%20can%20ask%20the%20state%20government%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20the%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20prior%20approval%20of%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20the%20NIA%20also%20has%20the%20power%20to%20transfer%20the%20entire%20case%2C%20including%20the%20responsibility%20for%20the%20investigation%20and%20trial%2C%20to%20the%20state%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20not%20all%20cases%20of%20the%20UAPA%20are%20investigated%20by%20the%20NIA%2C%20but%20even%20when%20a%20state%20government%20investigates%20these%20cases%2C%20it%20needs%20to%20follow%20the%20investigating%20procedure%20of%20the%20NIA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02151158%2FNIA-HQ.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22765%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02151158%2FNIA-HQ.jpg%20765w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02151158%2FNIA-HQ-300x225.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695385%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22574%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20NIA%20has%20jurisdiction%20to%20investigate%20terrorism%20cases%20under%20the%20UAPA.%20Photo%3A%20Pulakit%20Singh%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20the%20agency%20may%20seek%20assistance%20or%20cooperation%20from%20the%20government%20of%20the%20specific%20state%20where%20the%20offense%20took%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20mention%20here%20that%20the%20objective%20of%20the%20NIA%20Act%20was%20to%20constitute%20an%20investigating%20agency%20at%20the%20national%20level%20to%20investigate%20and%20prosecute%20offences%20affecting%20mainly%20the%20sovereignty%2C%20security%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20the%20security%20of%20the%20state%20and%20friendly%20relations%20with%20foreign%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nia.gov.in%2Fvision-mission.htm%5C%22%3EThe%20NIA%20aims%20to%20set%20the%20standards%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20excellence%20in%20counterterrorism%20and%20other%20national%20security-related%20investigations%20at%20the%20national%20level%20by%20developing%20into%20a%20highly%20trained%2C%20partnership-oriented%20workforce%2C%20and%20holds%20importance%20over%20state%20police%20due%20to%20its%20specialised%20mandate%20and%20jurisdiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESuperintendent%20of%20police%20has%20been%20given%20discretionary%20powers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20113%20of%20the%20BNS%20states%20that%20whether%20a%20person%20would%20be%20booked%20under%20the%20BNS%20or%20the%20UAPA%20for%20a%20terrorist%20act%20will%20be%20decided%20by%20an%20officer%20not%20below%20the%20rank%20of%20superintendent%20of%20police%20(SP).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20if%20an%20SP%20books%20a%20person%20under%20the%20BNS%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%20act%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20state%20police%20will%20investigate%20the%20offence.%20However%2C%20if%20booked%20under%20the%20UAPA%2C%20the%20NIA%20would%20investigate%20the%20same%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20arbitrary%20power%20given%20to%20the%20SP%2C%20which%20was%20earlier%20not%20found%20in%20the%20IPC%2C%20means%20that%20it%20is%20now%20up%20to%20the%20SP%20to%20decide%20whether%20an%20offence%20should%20be%20investigated%20by%20an%20agency%20as%20specialised%20as%20the%20NIA%20or%20by%20the%20state%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20discretionary%20authority%20vested%20in%20the%20SP%20raises%20concerns%20about%20potential%20arbitrariness%20in%20determining%20the%20course%20of%20the%20investigation%20and%20prosecution%20of%20offenses%20deemed%20as%20acts%20of%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pivotal%20issue%20lies%20in%20the%20subjective%20interpretation%20by%20SPs%20to%20selectively%20book%20people%20under%20either%20of%20the%20statutes.%20How%20is%20the%20SP%20supposed%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20book%20a%20person%20under%20the%20UAPA%20or%20the%20BNS%20when%20the%20definition%20of%20a%20terrorist%20act%20under%20both%20statutes%20is%20the%20same%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20absence%20of%20clear%20and%20objective%20criteria%20for%20invoking%20either%20of%20the%20statutes%20adds%20an%20element%20of%20ambiguity%20to%20the%20application%20of%20anti-terrorism%20laws.%C2%A0The%20expansion%20of%20the%20SP%E2%80%99s%20role%20from%20a%20law%20enforcement%20officer%20to%20a%20decision-maker%20with%20significant%20implications%20for%20the%20choice%20of%20investigative%20agencies%20introduces%20challenges%20to%20the%20uniform%20and%20impartial%20application%20of%20anti-terrorism%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20powers%20of%20an%20SP%20can%20be%20misused%20to%20selectively%20book%20under%20the%20UAPA%20or%20the%20BNS%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20further%20raises%20concerns%20regarding%20potential%20arbitrariness%2C%20favouritism%20and%20selective%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20a%20hypothetical%20scenario%20involving%20riots%20between%20Groups%20A%20and%20B%2C%20both%20potentially%20falling%20within%20the%20ambit%20of%20terrorist%20acts%2C%20the%20discretion%20granted%20to%20the%20SP%20becomes%20a%20pivotal%20factor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fuapa-anti-terrorism-laws%5C%22%3EThe%20UAPA%2C%20with%20its%20expansive%20powers%3C%2Fa%3E%20allowing%20searches%2C%20seizures%20and%20arrests%20based%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpersonal%20knowledge%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20police%20without%20judicial%20validation%2C%20has%20been%20criticised%20for%20potentially%20infringing%20upon%20the%20presumption%20of%20innocence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provisions%20of%20the%20Act%2C%20allowing%20action%20against%20individuals%20for%20acts%20deemed%20%E2%80%9Clikely%20to%20threaten%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Clikely%20to%20strike%20terror%E2%80%9D%2C%20raise%20concerns%20about%20the%20principle%20of%20proportionality%20in%20punishment.%20The%20recent%20cases%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmore-than-2500-activists-academics-others-issue-statement-demanding-stan-swamys-release%5C%22%3EFather%20Stanislaus%20Lourduswamy%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fu%3Eand%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwill-continue-my-fight-siddique-kappan-walks-out-of-jail-after-over-two-years%5C%22%3Ejournalist%20Siddique%20Kappan%3C%2Fa%3E%20highlight%20the%20far-reaching%20implications%20of%20the%20UAPA%E2%80%99s%20provisions%2C%20including%20prolonged%20detention%20without%20bail%20and%20extended%20periods%20of%20custody%20without%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbhima-koregaon-16-must-not-be-forgotten%5C%22%3EThe%20Elgar%20Parishad%2016%20Must%20Not%20Be%20Forgotten%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20potential%20for%20the%20abuse%20of%20these%20provisions%20underscores%20the%20need%20for%20a%20thought-through%20and%20principled%20approach%20in%20the%20application%20of%20anti-terrorism%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20situation%20where%20both%20Group%20A%20and%20B%20technically%20meet%20the%20definitions%20of%20offences%20punishable%20under%20both%20the%20UAPA%20and%20BNS%2C%20there%20is%20a%20risk%20of%20the%20SP%E2%80%99s%20decision%20being%20influenced%20by%20political%20considerations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuppose%20individuals%20from%20Group%20A%20are%20perceived%20as%20dissenting%20voices%20against%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20ideology.%20The%20SP%20may%20selectively%20book%20them%20under%20the%20UAPA%2C%20utilising%20its%20stringent%20provisions%20to%20keep%20them%20incarcerated%2C%20while%20the%20other%20group%20may%20be%20charged%20under%20the%20BNS.%20This%20creates%20potential%20for%20the%20legal%20framework%20to%20be%20manipulated%20for%20political%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%20of%20differential%20treatment%20based%20on%20ideological%20considerations%20poses%20a%20direct%20challenge%20to%20the%20principles%20of%20equality%20before%20the%20law%20and%20fairness%20in%20legal%20proceedings.%20The%20potential%20misuse%20of%20these%20powers%20could%20result%20in%20the%20suppression%20of%20dissenting%20voices%20and%20the%20erosion%20of%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20intertwining%20of%20terrorism%20clauses%20in%20general%20law%20and%20the%20discretionary%20powers%20granted%20to%20the%20SP%20necessitate%20a%20robust%20mechanism%20for%20accountability%2C%20oversight%20and%20adherence%20to%20legal%20principles.%20Striking%20a%20delicate%20balance%20between%20national%20security%20imperatives%20and%20safeguarding%20individual%20rights%20becomes%20paramount%20to%20ensure%20the%20fair%20and%20just%20application%20of%20anti-terrorism%20laws%2C%20preventing%20their%20misuse%20for%20political%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECould%20lead%20to%20jurisdictional%20manipulation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pivotal%20role%20of%20the%20SP%20in%20choosing%20between%20the%20UAPA%20and%20the%20BNS%20introduces%20a%20risk%20of%20jurisdictional%20manipulation%20for%20political%20purposes.%20As%20detailed%20above%2C%20in%20routine%20scenarios%2C%20the%20customary%20process%20involves%20the%20officer-in-charge%20forwarding%20a%20report%20to%20the%20state%20government%2C%20which%20then%20sends%20it%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20analysis%20and%20potential%20assignment%20to%20the%20NIA%20under%20the%20UAPA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20hypothetical%20scenario%2C%20where%20a%20terrorist%20act%20occurs%20in%20a%20state%2C%20say%20like%20West%20Bengal%2C%20which%20characterised%20by%20political%20discord%20between%20the%20state%20and%20Union%20governments%20due%20to%20differing%20ideologies%2C%20the%20potential%20for%20misuse%20becomes%20apparent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SP%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20register%20a%20case%20under%20either%20the%20UAPA%20or%20the%20BNS%20determines%20the%20course%20of%20investigation.%20Further%2C%20intentionally%20or%20otherwise%2C%20the%20state%20police%20may%20register%20the%20case%20under%20the%20BNS%20to%20retain%20jurisdictional%20control%20and%20prevent%20the%20case%20from%20being%20forwarded%20to%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20cases%20of%20political%20divergence%20between%20the%20state%20and%20Union%20governments%2C%20ego-driven%20reluctance%20to%20transfer%20the%20case%20to%20the%20NIA%20could%20pose%20a%20challenge%20to%20effectively%20addressing%20the%20menace%20of%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20scenario%20poses%20a%20significant%20challenge%2C%20potentially%20leading%20to%20an%20obstruction%20of%20the%20prescribed%20legal%20process.%20The%20risk%20of%20selective%20application%20of%20anti-terrorism%20laws%20based%20on%20political%20considerations%20may%20undermine%20the%20principles%20of%20fairness%2C%20equality%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20noteworthy%20that%20this%20issue%20may%20be%20less%20pronounced%20in%20states%20where%20the%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20share%20similar%20political%20affiliations%20or%20ideologies.%20However%2C%20in%20regions%20marked%20by%20political%20divergence%2C%20the%20potential%20for%20abuse%20of%20discretion%20in%20the%20application%20of%20anti-terrorism%20laws%20requires%20careful%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EConclusion%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20context%20where%20individuals%20are%20being%20subjectively%20and%20selectively%20charged%20under%20anti-terrorism%20or%20related%20laws%2C%20the%20courts%20lack%20authority%20to%20influence%20the%20choice%20of%20offences%20by%20the%20prosecuting%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judiciary%20has%20a%20limited%20role%20before%20the%20case%20comes%20to%20it.%C2%A0The%20court%E2%80%99s%20duty%20is%20to%20adjudicate%20the%20case%20based%20on%20the%20charges%20presented%2C%20ensuring%20a%20fair%20and%20lawful%20trial%20without%20intervening%20in%20the%20executive%E2%80%99s%20discretion%20in%20selecting%20specific%20charges%20against%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20of%20objects%20and%20reasons%20for%20passing%20these%20three%20criminal%20law%20Bills%20is%20that%20the%20government%20considers%20it%20expedient%20and%20necessary%20to%20review%20the%20existing%20criminal%20laws%20to%20strengthen%20law%20and%20order%20and%20also%20to%20focus%20on%20%E2%80%9Csimplifying%20legal%20procedure%20so%20that%20ease%20of%20living%20is%20ensured%20to%20the%20common%20%5Bperson%5D%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20we%20ask%20one%20simple%20question%20%E2%80%93%20will%20the%20common%20person%20have%20a%20better%20tomorrow%20with%20this%20duplication%3F%C2%A0You%20decide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESanjoy%20Ghose%20is%20a%20senior%20advocate%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20and%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court.%20Prakhar%20Bajpai%20is%20a%20law%20student%20at%20the%20National%20Law%20University%2C%20Punjab.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707392203000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F08%2F20135913%2Fscales-of-justice-flickr.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fduplication-or-duplicity%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20striking%20similarity%20in%20how%20a%20%E2%80%98terrorist%20act%E2%80%99%20is%20defined%20in%20the%20UAPA%20and%20the%20BNS%20allows%20th