fficiency%20upgrades.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENine%20states%20pledged%20to%20boost%20heat%20pump%20sales%20to%2065%25%20of%20the%20heating%20and%20cooling%20market%20by%202030.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20be%20the%20year%20to%20install%20an%20electric%20heat%20pump%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStates%20are%20expected%20to%20start%20doling%20out%20funding%20under%20a%20nearly%20%249%20billion%20rebate%20program%20later%20this%20year%20to%20make%20energy-efficient%20appliances%20and%20other%20home%20upgrades%20more%20affordable.%20Nine%20states%20on%20Wednesday%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nescaum.org%2Fdocuments%2F2.7.24-nescaum-mou-press-release.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealso%20pledged%20to%20aggressively%20promote%3C%2Fa%3E%20heat%20pumps%20so%20that%20by%202030%20they%20would%20account%20for%20a%20large%20majority%20of%20the%20market%20for%20heating%2C%20air%20conditioning%2C%20and%20water-heating%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20efforts%20are%20aimed%20at%20replacing%20oil%20and%20gas%20in%20residential%20buildings%2C%20a%20major%20contributor%20to%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20The%20energy%20Americans%20use%20at%20home%20accounts%20for%20about%2019%25%20of%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eia.gov%2Ftotalenergy%2Fdata%2Fmonthly%2Fpdf%2Fflow%2FCO2_emissions_2022.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Energy%20Information%20Administration%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElectric%20heat%20pumps%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Fenergysaver%2Fheat-pump-systems%23%3A~%3Atext%3DToday%2527s%2520heat%2520pump%2520can%2520reduce%2Cas%2520furnaces%2520and%2520baseboard%2520heaters.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emore%20efficient%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20heating%20and%20cooling%20homes%20than%20systems%20powered%20by%20oil%20and%20propane.%20Heat%20pumps%20move%20hot%20and%20cold%20air%20from%20indoors%20to%20outdoors%2C%20rather%20than%20burn%20fuel%2C%20and%20can%20save%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarbonswitch.com%2Fheat-pump-carbon-reduction-and-savings-potential-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20average%20US%20homeowner%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20estimated%20%24500%20a%20year.%20In%20Maine%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcities-require-or-encourage-switch-green-buildings-natural-gas-electric-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20leader%20in%20heat-pump%20adoption%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20thanks%20to%20state%20incentives%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mainehousing.org%2Fprograms-services%2Fenergy%2Fenergydetails%2Fheat-pump-program%23%3A~%3Atext%3DUsing%2520prices%2520from%2520the%2520Governor%2527s%2Ccompared%2520to%2520heating%2520with%2520propane.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eannual%20savings%20range%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20%24900%20and%20more%20than%20%242%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20thinking%20about%20ways%20to%20provide%20more%20incentives%20so%20that%20we%20can%20make%20the%20decision%20easier%20for%20consumers%20because%20heat%20pumps%20are%20not%20cheap%2C%26quot%3B%20Serena%20McIlwain%2C%20the%20secretary%20of%20the%20Maryland%20Department%20of%20the%20Environment%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20going%20to%20need%20some%20support%20from%20states%20and%20the%20federal%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaryland%20is%20among%20nine%20states%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20California%2C%20Colorado%2C%20Maine%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20New%20York%2C%20Oregon%2C%20and%20Rhode%20Island%20%E2%80%94%20that%20aim%20to%20boost%20heat-pump%20sales%20to%2065%25%20of%20new%20heating%2C%20air%20conditioning%2C%20and%20water-heating%20systems%20by%202030%20and%2090%25%20by%202040.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeat%20pumps%20currently%20make%20up%20about%20one-quarter%20of%20the%20HVAC%20market%20in%20those%20states%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Northeast%20States%20for%20Coordinated%20Air%20Use%20Management%2C%20a%20coalition%20of%20environmental%20agencies%20leading%20the%20multistate%20push%20to%20boost%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECutting%20the%20up-front%20costs%20of%20buying%20and%20installing%20heat%20pumps%20is%20a%20key%20way%20to%20increase%20sales.%20Prices%20vary%20widely%20depending%20on%20the%20project%2C%20including%20where%20someone%20lives%2C%20the%20size%20of%20their%20home%2C%20the%20type%20of%20heat%20pump%20they%20buy%2C%20and%20the%20labor.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rewiringamerica.org%2Felectrification-costs-estimates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereport%20by%20Rewiring%20America%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20advocates%20for%20electrifying%20buildings%2C%20found%20that%20median%20costs%20ranged%20from%20%245%2C200%20in%20Maine%20to%20more%20than%20%2418%2C000%20in%20Massachusetts%20before%20applying%20state%20incentives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFederal%20tax%20breaks%2C%20state%20rebates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20signed%20into%20law%20by%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20in%20August%202022%20authorized%20numerous%20programs%20to%20help%20homeowners%20go%20electric%20and%20invest%20in%20energy-efficient%20retrofits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20tax%20credit%20of%20up%20to%20%243%2C200%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irs.gov%2Fcredits-deductions%2Fenergy-efficient-home-improvement-credit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebecame%20available%20last%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20people%20making%20changes%20to%20their%20primary%20residence.%20However%2C%20the%20reach%20is%20limited%20because%20the%20credit%20can't%20be%20claimed%20by%20landlords%20or%20Americans%20who%20don't%20have%20much%20taxable%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20states%20are%20expected%20to%20set%20up%20rebate%20programs%20funded%20by%20the%20act.%20But%20first%2C%20the%20programs%20need%20approval%20from%20the%20Energy%20Department%2C%20and%20so%20far%20only%20California%2C%20New%20York%2C%20Hawaii%2C%20and%20New%20Mexico%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Fscep%2Farticles%2Ffirst-group-states-apply-landmark-home-energy-rebates-funding-lower-energy-costs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehave%20submitted%20their%20applications%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Maryland%20hopes%20to%20offer%20rebates%20by%20summer%20or%20fall%2C%20Jay%20Apperson%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20at%20the%20state's%20Department%20of%20the%20Environment%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20rebate%20program%20is%20designed%20to%20offer%20point-of-sale%20discounts%20on%20heat%20pumps%2C%20electric%20stoves%2C%20insulation%2C%20and%20new%20breaker%20boxes%20and%20wiring%20%E2%80%94%20capped%20at%20%2414%2C000%20per%20household.%20The%20program%20is%20targeted%20to%20low-%20and%20moderate-income%20homeowners%2C%20or%20those%20earning%20between%2080%25%20and%20150%25%20of%20the%20median%20income%20in%20their%20area.%20Landlords%20who%20rent%20to%20people%20in%20those%20income%20brackets%20are%20also%20eligible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20program%20is%20designed%20to%20cover%20half%20the%20cost%20of%20energy-efficiency%20projects%20that%20can%20show%20a%20home's%20energy%20use%20will%20drop%20by%20at%20least%2020%25%2C%20with%20larger%20rebates%20for%20low-income%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20rebate%20programs%20are%20a%20vehicle%20for%20equity%20in%20the%20IRA%2C%26quot%3B%20Sage%20Briscoe%2C%20the%20director%20of%20federal%20policy%20at%20Rewiring%20America%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20the%20tool%20to%20reach%20families%20most%20in%20need%20of%20help%20to%20make%20changes%20in%20their%20homes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20up-front%20costs%2C%20a%20barrier%20to%20increasing%20heat-pump%20adoption%20is%20education.%20Homeowners%20typically%20don't%20think%20about%20their%20heating%20and%20cooling%20system%20until%20it%20breaks.%20That%20leads%20to%20a%20mad%20dash%20to%20replace%20it%2C%20and%20many%20contractors%20still%20aren't%20familiar%20with%20heat-pump%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20that%20end-of-life%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20Emily%20Levin%2C%20a%20senior%20policy%20advisor%20of%20building%20electrification%20at%20NESCAUM%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20outdated%20information%20about%20heat%20pumps%20out%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcIlwain%20said%20Maryland%20was%20working%20to%20put%20more%20information%20online%2C%20including%20a%20database%20of%20contractors%2C%20electricians%2C%20and%20manufacturers%20trained%20on%20heat%20pumps.%20The%20website%20will%20also%20have%20information%20about%20incentives%20for%20homeowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStates%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.efficiencymaine.com%2Fabout-heat-pumps%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMaine%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcleanheat.ny.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENew%20York%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20California%20have%20already%20set%20up%20similar%20sites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiscounts-on-energy-efficient-home-upgrades-biden-ira-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707387962000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c3e3ff6fcb546d2d4d35c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiscounts-on-energy-efficient-home-upgrades-biden-ira-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Electric%20heat%20pumps%20can%20save%20the%20average%20US%20homeowner%20an%20estimated%20%24500%20a%20year.%20New%20discounts%20are%20coming%20nationwide.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cboudreau%40insider.com%20(Catherine%20Boudreau)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A37%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%