ractured%20into%20smaller%20and%20smaller%20niches.%20The%20NFL%20and%20college%20football%20have%20continued%20to%20be%20extraordinarily%20strong%20from%20an%20audience%20perspective%2C%20said%20Brian%20Fuhrer%2C%20the%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20product%20leadership%20at%20Nielsen%2C%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20big%20reasons.%20One%2C%20sports%20fans%20will%20go%20to%20great%20lengths%20(including%20piracy)%20to%20find%20the%20content%20they're%20looking%20for.%20Two%2C%20the%20NFL%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20does%20a%20lot%20to%20cater%20to%20its%20audience.%20%26quot%3BThe%20NFL%20has%20done%2C%20I%20think%2C%20a%20really%20good%20job%20of%20continuing%20to%20evolve%20their%20product%20to%20make%20it%20as%20TV-friendly%20as%20it%20can%20be%20and%20give%20each%20city%20and%20region%20teams%20that%20they%20seem%20to%20continue%20to%20really%20engage%20with%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20really%20have%20a%20driving%20force%20of%20bringing%20audiences%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProfessional%20football%20also%20has%20the%20advantage%20of%20feeling%20like%20an%20event.%20The%20season%20has%20fewer%20games%20than%20basketball%20or%20baseball%2C%20and%20they're%20clustered%20mostly%20on%20one%20blockbuster%20day%20every%20week.%20If%20you're%20an%20NFL%20fan%2C%20you've%20got%20just%2017%20chances%20to%20see%20your%20team%20play%20in%20the%20regular%20season%2C%20so%20they're%20all%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20special%20occasion.%20NBA%20and%20MLB%20teams%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20play%2082%20and%20162%20regular-season%20games%2C%20respectively.%20This%20eventizing%20means%20more%20people%20schedule%20their%20lives%20around%20the%20sport%3A%20The%20NFL%20picks%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sportsmediawatch.com%2F2023%2F02%2Fsuper-bowl-out-of-home-viewing-impact%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eout-of-home%20viewing%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20means%20more%20people%20go%20out%20to%20bars%20and%20gather%20in%20groups%20to%20watch%20big%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NFL%20also%20benefits%20from%20the%20deference%20that%20networks%20show%20the%20league.%20Broadcast's%20core%20audience%20is%20typically%20older%2C%20so%20when%20NFL%20games%20come%20on%20in%20the%20fall%20it%20draws%20younger%20viewers%20back%20in.%20That%20gives%20networks%20an%20opportunity%20to%20promote%20their%20other%20content%2C%20like%20the%20Grammys%20or%20%26quot%3BThe%20Masked%20Singer%26quot%3B%20or%20one%20of%20those%20indiscernible%20crime%20dramas.%20This%20trickle-down%20value%20to%20other%20content%20means%20networks%20are%20deferential%20to%20the%20league.%20They're%20not%20eager%20to%20counterprogram%20big%20games%2C%20which%20their%20programming%20would%20lose%20against%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20viewer%20behavior%2C%20the%20product%20itself%20has%20been%20on%20the%20upswing%20for%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20said%20Jon%20Lewis%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Sports%20Media%20Watch%2C%20which%20tracks%20the%20sports%20media%20industry.%20It%20has%20benefited%20from%20a%20crop%20of%20star%20young%20quarterbacks%20like%20Patrick%20Mahomes%2C%20Josh%20Allen%2C%20and%20Lamar%20Jackson.%20New%20rivalries%20have%20emerged%2C%20and%20teams%20that%20haven't%20historically%20been%20very%20successful%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Buffalo%20Bills%2C%20the%20Detroit%20Lions%2C%20the%20Chiefs%20%E2%80%94%20have%20had%20good%20runs.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20golden%20age%20for%20the%20NFL%2C%26quot%3B%20Lewis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NFL%20has%20managed%20to%20move%20past%20controversies.%20You%20rarely%20hear%20about%20players%20kneeling%20during%20the%20national%20anthem%20anymore%2C%20and%20fans%20seem%20determined%20to%20largely%20ignore%20many%20issues%20that%20plague%20the%20sport%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nih.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnih-research-matters%2Fhow-football-raises-risk-chronic-traumatic-encephalopathy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECTE%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkirsten-gillibrand-nfl-ray-rice-domestic-violence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edomestic%20abuse%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Will%20Smith's%202015%20movie%20%26quot%3BConcussion%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20dangers%20of%20the%20sport%20didn't%20change%20things%2C%20nor%20did%20the%202014%20video%20of%20Ravens%20running%20back%20Ray%20Rice%20assaulting%20his%20then-fianc%C3%A9e.%20The%20league%20has%20been%20able%20to%20make%20brief%20gestures%20toward%20the%20issues%20and%20then%20wait%20out%20the%20clock%20until%20the%20discussion%20moves%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20national%20pastime%2C%26quot%3B%20Lewis%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20NFL%20tied%20itself%20into%20the%20American%20self-image%2C%20tied%20itself%20into%20the%20Americana%20in%20a%20way%20that%20really%20only%20baseball%20decades%20ago%20was%20able%20to%20do.%20It's%20the%20last%20mass%20event%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20last%20mass%20gathering%20on%20television%20that%20we%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pace%20of%20the%20NFL's%20ratings%20growth%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%20won't%20last%20forever.%20In%20part%2C%20the%20league's%20recent%20successes%20have%20just%20been%20making%20up%20for%20a%20downturn%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnfl-ratings-down-for-2016-and-might-continue-to-slump-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2016-2017%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnfl-ratings-fall-still-dominate-prime-time-2018-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2017-2018%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20seasons.%20The%20explanation%20at%20the%20time%20for%20those%20declines%20was%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnfl-ratings-spike-trump-wild-card-weekend-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20taking%20a%20lot