irst%2C%20King%20Charles%20can%20delegate%20some%20or%20most%20of%20his%20royal%20functions%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.legislation.gov.uk%2Fukpga%2FEdw8and1Geo6%2F1%2F16%2Fsection%2F6%5C%22%3Ecounsellors%20of%20state%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20happens%20most%20commonly%20when%20he%20is%20travelling%20overseas.%20Two%20counsellors%20of%20state%20act%20jointly%20in%20exercising%20royal%20powers%20such%20as%20assenting%20to%20laws%2C%20receiving%20ambassadors%20and%20holding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommonslibrary.parliament.uk%2Fresearch-briefings%2Fcbp-7460%2F%5C%22%3EPrivy%20Council%3C%2Fa%3E%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.royal.uk%2Fcounsellors-of-state%5C%22%3Ecounsellors%20of%20state%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20the%20spouse%20of%20the%20sovereign%20and%20the%20next%20four%20adults%20in%20line%20of%20succession%20to%20the%20throne%20%E2%80%93%20being%20Queen%20Camilla%2C%20Prince%20William%2C%20Prince%20Harry%2C%20Prince%20Andrew%20and%20Princess%20Beatrice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Prince%20Harry%20is%20excluded%20while%20he%20is%20outside%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20and%20in%20practice%20Prince%20Andrew%20and%20Princess%20Beatrice%20are%20not%20called%20on%20to%20act%20as%20they%20are%20not%20%E2%80%9Cworking%20royals%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20this%20left%20only%20Queen%20Camilla%20and%20Prince%20William%20to%20perform%20the%20role%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.legislation.gov.uk%2Fukpga%2F2022%2F47%2F2022-12-07%2Fdata.html%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DAn%2520Act%2520to%2520add%2520His%2Cdelegated%2520as%2520Counsellors%2520of%2520State.%5C%22%3Elaw%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20passed%20in%20the%20UK%20in%202022%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommonslibrary.parliament.uk%2Fcreating-more-counsellors-of-state%2F%5C%22%3Eadd%20Princess%20Anne%20and%20Prince%20Edward%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECounsellors%20of%20state%20may%20carry%20out%20most%20of%20the%20sovereign%E2%80%99s%20functions%20while%20he%20is%20ill%2C%20but%20they%20cannot%20dissolve%20parliament%2C%20except%20on%20his%20instruction%2C%20and%20they%20cannot%20create%20peers.%20Whether%20they%20can%20appoint%20a%20prime%20minister%20remains%20a%20matter%20of%20debate.%20Most%20significantly%2C%20they%20cannot%20exercise%20powers%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20King%E2%80%99s%20other%20realms%2C%20such%20as%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERegency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20option%20is%20a%20regency.%20This%20occurs%20if%20the%20King%20%E2%80%9Cis%20by%20reason%20of%20infirmity%20of%20mind%20or%20body%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.legislation.gov.uk%2Fukpga%2FEdw8and1Geo6%2F1%2F16%2Fsection%2F2%5C%22%3Eincapable%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20time%20being%20of%20performing%20the%20royal%20functions%E2%80%9D.%20The%20sovereign%20does%20not%20control%20when%20or%20for%20how%20long%20a%20regency%20occurs.%20Instead%2C%20it%20is%20initiated%20by%20a%20declaration%20of%20three%20or%20more%20of%3A%20the%20sovereign%E2%80%99s%20spouse%2C%20the%20lord%20chancellor%2C%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%2C%20the%20lord%20chief%20justice%20of%20England%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.judiciary.uk%2Fabout-the-judiciary%2Fwho-are-the-judiciary%2Fjudges%2Fprofile-mor%2F%5C%22%3Emaster%20of%20the%20rolls%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%E2%80%99s%20Regency%20Act%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.legislation.gov.uk%2Fukpga%2FEdw8and1Geo6%2F1%2F16%2Fsection%2F3%5C%22%3Erequires%3C%2Fa%3E%20Prince%20William%20to%20be%20regent%2C%20as%20he%20is%20the%20next%20adult%20in%20line%20of%20succession%20to%20the%20crown.%20The%20regent%20has%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20King%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20but%20cannot%20change%20the%20order%20of%20succession%20to%20the%20crown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Regency%20Act%20does%20not%20give%20the%20regent%20powers%20in%20relation%20to%20realms%20such%20as%20Australia%20and%20New%20Zealand.%20New%20Zealand%20resolved%20the%20problem%20by%20inserting%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.legislation.govt.nz%2Fact%2Fpublic%2F1986%2F0114%2Flatest%2FDLM94216.html%5C%22%3Esection%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20its%20Constitution%20Act%20which%20provides%20that%20whoever%20is%20made%20regent%20under%20the%20law%20of%20the%20UK%20may%20perform%20the%20royal%20functions%20of%20the%20sovereign%20with%20respect%20to%20New%20Zealand.%20Australia%2C%20however%2C%20has%20done%20nothing%20in%20this%20regard%2C%20so%20a%20British%20regent%20would%20have%20no%20powers%20with%20respect%20to%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbdication%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20option%20for%20an%20incapacitated%20monarch%20is%20abdication.%20This%20leads%20to%20difficult%20questions%20about%20how%20an%20abdication%20would%20operate%20in%20relation%20to%20each%20of%20the%20realms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20King%20Edward%20VIII%20abdicated%20in%201936%2C%20it%20was%20achieved%20by%20both%20a%20signed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalarchives.gov.uk%2Feducation%2Fresources%2Fsignificant-events%2Fabdication-of-edward-viii-1936%2F%5C%22%3Einstrument%20of%20abdication%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20enactment%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.legislation.gov.uk%2Fukpga%2FEdw8and1Geo6%2F1%2F3%2Fenacted%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3D(1)Immediately%2520upon%2520the%2520Royal%2Cand%2520there%2520shall%2520be%2520a%5C%22%3Elegislation%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20which%20the%20various%20realms%2C%20including%20Australia%2C%20assented.%20This%20is%20not%20possible%20today%2C%20as%20the%20UK%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww6.austlii.edu.au%2Fcgi-bin%2Fviewdoc%2Fau%2Flegis%2Fcth%2Fnum_act%2Faa1986114%2Fs1.html%5C%22%3Eno%20longer%20legislate%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20respect%20to%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbdication%20would%20therefore%20raise%20difficult%20questions%20about%20whether%20there%20needed%20to%20be%20a%20separate%20abdication%20of%20the%20King%20of%20Australia%2C%20to%20trigger%20the%20application%20of%20the%20rules%20of%20succession%20that%20are%20now%20part%20of%20Australian%20law%2C%20or%20whether%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.austlii.edu.au%2Fcgi-bin%2Fviewdoc%2Fau%2Flegis%2Fcth%2Fconsol_act%2Fcoaca430%2Fs2.html%5C%22%3Ecovering%20clause%202%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20which%20defines%20the%20sovereign%20by%20reference%20to%20Queen%20Victoria%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cheirs%20and%20successors%20in%20the%20sovereignty%20of%20the%20United%20Kingdom%E2%80%9D%2C%20would%20apply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20potential%20constitutional%20messiness%20of%20dealing%20with%20the%20King%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20his%2014%20realms%20beyond%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20it%20is%20likely%20abdication%20would%20be%20avoided.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsequences%20for%20Australia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20King%20Charles%20were%20incapacitated%20and%20counsellors%20of%20state%20or%20a%20regent%20were%20appointed%2C%20would%20this%20cause%20any%20real%20problem%20in%20Australia%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20King%E2%80%99s%20only%20remaining%20substantial%20powers%20with%20respect%20to%20Australia%20are%20the%20appointment%20and%20removal%20of%20the%20governor-general%20and%20the%20state%20governors.%20The%20governor-general%E2%80%99s%20term%20is%20expected%20to%20expire%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20year.%20If%20King%20Charles%20were%20then%20seriously%20ill%20and%20unable%20to%20appoint%20a%20new%20governor-general%2C%20no%20one%20could%20do%20so%2C%20as%20neither%20counsellors%20of%20state%20nor%20a%20regent%20could%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20current%20governor-general%2C%20David%20Hurley%2C%20could%20choose%20to%20continue%20in%20office%2C%20as%20there%20is%20no%20formal%20termination%20of%20his%20office%20until%20he%20is%20replaced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlternatively%2C%20he%20could%20resign%20and%20his%20office%20could%20be%20filled%20on%20a%20temporary%20basis%20by%20a%20state%20governor%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.austlii.edu.au%2Fcgi-bin%2Fviewdoc%2Fau%2Flegis%2Fcth%2Fconsol_act%2Fcoaca430%2Fxx4.html%5C%22%3Eadministrator%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20is%20the%20usual%20practice%20when%20there%20is%20a%20vacancy%20in%20the%20office.%20If%20the%20office%20of%20a%20state%20governor%20becomes%20vacant%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.governor.nsw.gov.au%2Fgovernor%2Flieutenant-governor%2Frole-of-the-lieutenant-governor%2F%5C%22%3Elieutenant-governor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20is%20often%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20state%2C%20can%20exercise%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20functions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20a%20regency%20were%20to%20continue%20for%20a%20long%20time%20%E2%80%93%20perhaps%20years%20%E2%80%93%20this%20could%20become%20unsustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20consideration%20is%20that%20if%20there%20is%20a%20regency%2C%20there%20is%20no%20power%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theaustralian.com.au%2Fnational-affairs%2Fopinion%2Fin-race-to-palace-governor-general-has-inside-running%2Fnews-story%2Fd3918f42af1d081f203daa65f5b53e0f%5C%22%3Edismiss%20a%20governor-general%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20if%20a%20constitutional%20crisis%20arose%2C%20such%20as%20that%20in%201975%20with%20the%20dismissal%20of%20the%20Whitlam%20government%2C%20the%20governor-general%20would%20know%20that%20he%20or%20she%20could%20act%20without%20the%20prospect%20of%20dismissal%20on%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20prime%20minister.%20This%20unbalances%20the%20constitutional%20pressures%20that%20are%20deliberately%20built%20into%20the%20system%2C%20giving%20a%20stronger%20hand%20to%20the%20governor-general%20and%20weakening%20the%20position%20of%20the%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmichaelwest.com.au%2Fking-charles-illness-affects-australia%2F%5C%22%3Eproblem%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20addressed%20in%20the%20same%20way%20as%20the%20rules%20of%20succession%20to%20the%20throne%20were%20changed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.legislation.gov.au%2FC2015A00023%2Fasmade%2Ftext%5C%22%3Ein%202015%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20remove%20gender%20discrimination.%20It%20would%20involve%20each%20state%20enacting%20a%20law%20requesting%20the%20Commonwealth%20to%20enact%20a%20law%20that%20recognised%20the%20authority%20of%20a%20regent%20to%20exercise%20the%20sovereign%E2%80%99s%20powers%20with%20respect%20to%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20is%20not%20essential%20to%20fix%20this%20problem%2C%20it%20would%20still%20be%20wise%2C%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20orderly%20constitutional%20housekeeping%2C%20to%20address%20it%20before%20any%20real%20difficulties%20arise.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F222870%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fanne-twomey-6072%5C%22%3EAnne%20Twomey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20emerita%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-sydney-841%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Sydney%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwhat-happens-if-king-charles-can-no-longer-perform-his-duties-222870%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707385858000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F15134341%2F22.2.22-46.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhat-happens-if-king-charles-can-no-longer-perform-his-d